      "id": "a35de33f_1650f9d8",
      "file_path": "src/main/resources/application.yml",
      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 67,
      "message": "Amm.. for test yaml its not required at the moment.\nThe reason I introduced this is coz I was seeing some exceptions in our logs when the kafkalistener was converting the binary event from the wire to an actual pojo object.\n\nIn theory , the reason why this is added is : \"The FAIL_ON_EMPTY_BEANS serialization feature defines what happens when no accessors (properties) for a type are found. If enabled (the default), an exception is thrown to indicate that the bean is non-serializable. If disabled, a bean is serialized as an empty Object with no properties. \"",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7965,
        "name": "Priyank Maheshwari",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "priyank.maheshwari@est.tech",
        "username": "mpriyank"
